  "body": "Both `SECP256K1.class` and `AltBN128AddPrecompiledContract.class` have a Java implementation and another one using native libraries. The native library implementations are enabled by default in both cases. `BesuCommand` has the options `--Xsecp256k1-native-enabled` and `--Xaltbn128-native-enabled` which can be set to `false` to disable the native libraries and use the Java implementations. \r\n\r\nBut right now the disabling of the libraries does not work:\r\n\r\n`SECP256K1.class` and `AltBN128AddPrecompiledContract.class` have a boolean flag to enable or disable the native libraries, which is initialized with `true`:\r\n```\r\nprivate boolean useNative = true;\r\n```\r\n\r\nIn `BesuCommand` the handling of the options looks like this:\r\n```\r\n  private void configureNativeLibs() {\r\n    if (unstableNativeLibraryOptions.getNativeAltbn128()) {\r\n      AbstractAltBnPrecompiledContract.enableNative();\r\n    }\r\n    if (unstableNativeLibraryOptions.getNativeSecp256k1()) {\r\n      SignatureAlgorithmFactory.getInstance().enableNative();\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n```\r\n\r\n`unstableNativeLibraryOptions.getNativeAltbn128()` and `unstableNativeLibraryOptions.getNativeSecp256k1()` return `true` by default and `false` when one of the corresponding options is set to `false`.\r\n\r\nIf one of the options is set to `false` in the command line, it simply skips the `enableNative` function call, but because the `useNative` variable is initialized with `true`, it never changes to `false`. There is also no other function available to set it to `false`. Because `useNative` can never be changed to `false` the native library implementations are always used.\r\n\r\nI would suggest to initialize `useNative` with `false`. The native libraries would still be enabled by default, because in `BesuCommand` the `enableNative` functions will be called by default and set `useNative` to `true`. But if `--Xsecp256k1-native-enabled` or `--Xaltbn128-native-enabled` are set to `false` the `enableNative` functions will not be called and `useNative` stays `false` which is the intended behavior.\r\n\r\nPlease tell me your thoughts about the suggested change. ",
